      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/123/5540",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ أَقَرَّ لِوَارِثٍ لَهُ وَ هُوَ مَرِيضٌ بِدَيْنٍ عَلَيْهِ فَقَالَ \"يَجُوزُ إِذَا كَانَ اَلَّذِي أَقَرَّ بِهِ دُونَ اَلثُّلُثِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5540 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Hisham ibn Salim from Isma'il ibn Jabir, who said: I asked Abu Abdullah (as), about a man who, while ill and in debt, acknowledged a right for one of his heirs.\nImam (as) said: \"It is permissible if what he acknowledged is less than one-third (of his wealth).\""
        ]
      }
    },
